 MBOMBELA – A quick response by members of the South African Police Service, as well as the White River Flying Squad, led to the arrest of four suspects around 08:30 this morning. Also read: Suspected poachers arrested despite pursuing aircraft going down The members reacted swiftly following a tip-off of a robbery in progress at a butchery in Bester Street. The suspects, aged between 26 and 33, are reported to have stormed the butchery and held members of staff at gunpoint before starting to steal meat. Public warned, child almost taken in Mbombela The suspects are facing charges of  business robbery and possession of three unlicensed firearms. A police investigation is underway to determine whether the suspects are involved in other crimes. 